President Obama has announced his intent to nominate David Danielson as Assistant Secretary for Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy at the Department of Energy. Dr. Danielson is currently a Program Director at the U.S. Department of Energy's Advanced Research Projects Agency-Energy (ARPA-E). He has also worked as a clean energy venture capitalist and co-founded the New England Clean Energy Council. Dr. Danielson has a strong background in clean energy technology and has authored numerous scientific articles in the field of advanced materials.

President Obama also announced his intent to nominate Dot Harris as Director of the Office of Minority Economic Impact at the Department of Energy. Ms. Harris is currently the President and CEO of Jabo Industries, LLC, a management consulting firm focused on the energy, information technology, and healthcare industries. She has previously held leadership positions at General Electric and ABB Service, Inc. Ms. Harris has a background in electrical engineering and technology management.

Both nominees have extensive experience in their respective fields and have demonstrated a commitment to advancing clean energy and promoting minority economic impact.